Upon startup, Jenkins will run $JENKINS_HOME/init.groovy.d/*.groovy scripts 

Meanwhile, "Jenkins is getting ready..." message is displayed

Drop files, restart Jenkins

Allows you to preconfigure everything --

without the GUIinit.groovy.d d

References
https://github.com/Accenture/adop-jenkins/blob/master/resources/init.groovy.d/adop_ldap.groovy
http://tdongsi.github.io/blog/2017/12/30/groovy-hook-script-and-jenkins-configuration-as-code/

